      <updated>2020-06-05T00:00:00+01:00</updated>
      <id>http://www.bnlawrence.net//academic/2020/06/software3</id>
      <content type="html" xml:base="http://www.bnlawrence.net//academic/2020/06/software3/">&lt;p&gt;So far in this series on scientific software, I discussed the notion that it might not be that easy to &lt;a href=&quot;/academic/2020/05/software1/&quot;&gt;define quality for scientific code&lt;/a&gt; (and left some questions hanging about how we might do that), and introduced some &lt;a href=&quot;/academic/2020/06/software2/&quot;&gt;scope questions&lt;/a&gt; about what we mean by science code, and did that by producing a big diagram with lots of stuff.&lt;/p&gt;</content>

      
      
      
      
      

